{"id":2314,"date":"2022-12-05T10:58:16","date_gmt":"2022-12-05T10:58:16","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/edgeonservices.com\/\/?p=2314"},"modified":"2023-10-25T06:30:48","modified_gmt":"2023-10-25T06:30:48","slug":"exploring-government-schemes-and-programs-for-a-better-future","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/edgeonservices.com\/exploring-government-schemes-and-programs-for-a-better-future\/","title":{"rendered":"Exploring Government Schemes and Programs for a Better Future"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>There are various government&nbsp;scholarship schemes provided for youth &amp; students.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\">I- Gov of India centralized web portal<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>The government of India has started a portal which cover all the government related information in a single window now any body can easily understand the various government services provided under a single website you may click the&nbsp;below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed\">https:\/\/india.gov.in\/<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\">II- Ministry of minority affairs<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ministry of Minority Affairs focuses towards issues relating to the minority communities namely Muslim, Christian, Buddhist, Sikhs, Parsis and Jain. The mandate of the Ministry includes formulation of overall policy and planning, coordination, evaluation and review of the regulatory framework and development programmes for the benefit of the minority communities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>http:\/\/www.minorityaffairs.gov.in\/schemesperformance<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\">III- Ministry of Human resource development<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>The main focus of this ministry is to develop the human capital of India which is its citizens, the main tool to achieve this is through education &amp; government&nbsp;scholarship schemes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main objectives of the Ministry&nbsp;is<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>1- Provide financial help in the form of scholarships, loan subsidy, etc to deserving students from deprived sections of the society.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>2- Formulating the National Policy on Education and to ensure that it is implemented in letter and spirit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>3- Planned development, including expanding access and improving quality of the educational institutions throughout the country, including in the regions where people do not have easy access to education.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>4- Paying special attention to disadvantaged groups like the poor, females and the minorities.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>5- Encouraging international cooperation in the field of education, including working closely with the UNESCO and foreign governments as well as Universities, to enhance the educational opportunities in the country, for more information please click the link&nbsp;below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>http:\/\/mhrd.gov.in\/schemes<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\">IV- Ministry of youth affairs and sports<\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>The Ministry of Youth Affairs &amp; Sports as the name suggest focus on youth &amp; sports please click the link below for more information.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>There are various government&nbsp;scholarship schemes provided for youth &amp; students. I- Gov of India centralized web portal The government of India has started a portal which cover all the government related information in a single window now any body can easily understand the various government services provided under a single website you may click the&nbsp;below. [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1508,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"","ast-site-content-layout":"","site-content-style":"default","site-sidebar-style":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","a